    • Method Detail

      • applicableAnnotations

        default java.util.Set<java.lang.String> applicableAnnotations()
        Returns:
        any other applicable annotations you want to process.

      • applicable

        default boolean applicable(Property property)
        This is for checking if a given `Property` is applicable for this extension. For instance, a nullability extension would check if the property was a non-primitive/non-Void type.
        Parameters:
        property - the property to check
        Returns:
        true if applicable, false if not.

      • generateValidation

        @Nullable
default com.squareup.javapoet.CodeBlock generateValidation(Property prop,
                                                                     java.lang.String propertyName,
                                                                     com.squareup.javapoet.ParameterSpec typeInstance)
        This is for generating your actual validation. This uses a JavaPoet CodeBlock, and gives you information about three parameters:
        Parameters:
        prop - the property itself
        propertyName - the name of the property being validated. If you are validating a `Person`'s `name` property, this is `name`
        typeInstance - the instance of the type being validated. If you are validating a `Person` instance, this is the instance as passed to the `validate` method.
        Returns:
        a codeblock of validation logic to execute, or null if there is none.

      • priority

        default InspectorExtension.Priority priority()
        This for declaring priority of your extension. This is useful if you have higher priority validation that should run as early as possible (such as nullability). Most validations should not care what order they are run in though. Default is InspectorExtension.Priority.NONE.
        Returns:
        the priority
